        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 29 at 1:45PM MDT by NWS Great Falls MT</headline>
        <description>At 143 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking strong thunderstorms along
a line extending from 10 miles east of Lima to 7 miles southwest of
Monida. Movement was east at 10 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Lima, Monida, Snowline, and Monida Pass.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
